comment_data.body:
@fmmarzoa could you follow these steps to send us verbose logs?
1. Enable verbose logging (Preferences > Languages & Frameworks > Flutter, under 'General')
2. Reproduce this issue
3. Find the logs in Help > Show log in finder (should be called `idea.log`)

Hey @helin24,

Find the requested log attached.

BTW, I found out it happens also when using an actual Android device connected to my laptop, so the device seems not to be relevant.

Kind Regards,
Fran

**(DELETED INVALID LOG HERE)**

@fmmarzoa okay, it makes sense this would not be device-specific. However, I don't see anything about the flutter plugin or jxbrowser inside the log you attached and it seems to be from March instead of recently. I'm not sure how to fix that assuming you saw flutter functionality in the IDE and followed the logging instructions above. Perhaps restart your IDE and verify the logging setup, then make sure the `idea.log` file is receiving new logs?

@helin24 find attached a log I just got a minute ago. I deleted all the previous idea.log files in my system first to make sure I got the right one this time, so I hope this time is right... :)

[idea.zip](https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/files/6720199/idea.zip)
@fmmarzoa thanks! I see the logs we're expecting. I don't notice anything suspect from first glance, but I'm hoping that the JxBrowser team will have more insight about why this might be happening.

@fmmarzoa I made a change hoping to address this problem but I don't have a physical linux device to test. This change should be available in the dev version of our plugin if you want to try it out and let me know if you continue to have this problem: https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/wiki/Dev-Channel
@helin24 Thanks! Sure, I'll be glad to give it a try ASAP. I'll keep you updated.

@helin24 just tried 59.0.1-dev.3 version following those instructions and I'm sorry to inform you that it did **not** solve the issue.

![Screenshot from 2021-07-20 19-50-10](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6368385/126371779-efea6010-fd0c-417d-a00b-f097d7670e51.png)
@fmmarzoa thanks for checking! Sorry to hear it didn't fix the problem; I'll keep investigating.
